Missing uncontrolled items. LEAs acquire ownership of uncontrolled items after one year and do not need to report possession for inventories. The more recent agency-level data therefore cannot account for all uncontrolled items. As above, it is difficult to evaluate the extent of this problem, but Fig. 2 shows how widespread the data discrepancies are. While missing uncontrolled items is a less theoretically interesting problem, it is an issue of consistency across SME transfer datasets and represents a limitation for working with recent inventory data.

