Discussion
Militarization is a part of modern policing. In the United States, intergovernmental aid, particularly the transfer of SME from the Department of Defense to police departments and sheriffs’ offices, contributes to the militarization of local law enforcement. Such equipment includes vehicles, weapons and attire more traditionally associated with military combat and interstate conflict, along with a range of other surplus goods.
Militarization of policing raises normative concerns. Many concerns in the United States involve the consequences of the shift in how police appear and behave, especially when their appearance

